post_text:
Comunidad y familia de nuestra escuela ESPERANZA,

We are super excited about welcoming our student on Monday, August 24th. Please remind students of the following NEW EXPECTATIONS:
1. School begins at 8:15AM and students must arrive at or after 8:00AM. Students will not be marked LATE UNTIL AFTER 8:30AM. All students who arrive between 8AM-8:30AM will receive free breakfast, as always. If students arrive before 8:00AM, they will need to wait inside their vehicle.
2. All students must wear a mask and keep it on ALL DAY, except when they eat.
3. Students will disinfect and/or wash their hands a minimum of three times per day.
4. Students must have their own school supplies to reduce or eliminate the need to share pencils, paper, scissors, etc.
5. All students will be asked to sanitize their belongings and their hands often throughout the day.
6. School ends at 1:15PM Monday-Thursday
7. THERE IS NOT IN-PERSON CLASSES ON FRIDAY
8. Seventy percent of all classwork MUST be completed on time.

Feliz D√≠a de las Madres
Happy Mother's Day
Este proyecto tom√≥ dias para ejecutarse y nunca pens√© que iban a participar tantas familias. En el comienzo notar√°n que incluimos fotogranf√≠as de todos y cada uno de quienes deseamos participar. La segunda parte son videos de nuestros ni√±os cant√°ndole a sus mam√°s, abuelas, o miembros de su familia y al ver el orgullo en las caras de las mam√°s, pues me hicieron llorar. ¬°Asombrozo y escalofriante como siempre! Gracias a todos que lo hicieron posible.
This project took days to put together and I never thought that so many families would take the time to participate. The first part includes pictures of anyone in the school who wished to participate. The second part includes videos of our children singing to their moms, grandmas, or family members. and seeing the pride on mom's faces, made me cry. AMAZING AS ALWAYS!. Thank you to all who made it possible.

post_text:
WINTER FESTIVAL
THURSDAY, DECEMBER 5, 2019 6pm-7pm

Our Students have worked arduously to be ready for this annual event. Please support our students by following these expectations.

Formal Public Events Etiquette
Arrive and be seated at least five minutes before the performances begin.
If late, please enter between performances.
Avoid making noises, if necessary, unwrap throat lozenges, mints or gum before the performance begins.
Do not talk with your fellow audience members during the play.
Turn off cell phones and other electronic device which might cause a distraction during the performance.
Remove your hat during performance to help guests behind see performances.
Remain in your seats, unless you have an emergency.
Sing along, or participate with performers only when requested.
Stand up if someone needs to pass in front of your seat.
Keep aisles or doorways clear at all times.
Remain seated until the houselights come up and wait for guests in front of you to exit first.
Take anything around you, including programs.

What is SafeUT Crisis Chat & Tip Line?
The SafeUT Crisis Chat and Tip Line is a statewide service that provides real-time crisis intervention to youth through live chat and a confidential tip program ‚Äì right from your smartphone.
Licensed clinicians in our 24/7 CrisisLine call center respond to all incoming chats and calls by providing:
‚Ä¢ supportive or crisis counseling,
‚Ä¢ suicide prevention, and
‚Ä¢ referral services.
We can help anyone with emotional crises, bullying, relationship problems, mental health, or suicide-related issues.
https://healthcare.utah.edu/uni/safe-ut/

Job Title Substitute Teachers K-6 hourly pay range $12/hr. to $20/hr. based on education and experience
Employer Esperanza Elementary School
Location 4956 West 3500 South West Valley City, Utah 84120

# Open Positions 2

Job Type Part-time on call

Job Description Esperanza Elementary School, a well-established charter school in West Valley City, is now accepting applications for substitute teachers for grades ranging from K-6th. Substitutes work on an as needed basis.
Job Qualifications Candidates wanting to substitute teach at Esperanza must have a high school diploma and some additional training or experience working with children. Candidates with an Associate Degree are preferred. Experience working with groups of children, good communication/organization skills, and a professional demeanor are also preferred. Candidates selected to substitute teach at the school are required to pass a criminal background check.

Applicant Requirements: Authorized to work in United States

Contact Eulogio Alejandre 801-305-1450 X 304

Application Deadline Open Until Filled

Esperanza Elementary
March 28, 2019 at 9:04 PM ¬∑

Dear Families,
We would like to invite you to our mariachi fundraiser on April 17th at El Paisa Grill located at 2126 south 3200 west, West Valley City. We will be raising funds for our Esperanza Elementary mariachi band. (The first child mariachi of the state of Utah). El Paisa Grill will donate 50% of their earnings for that day to our mariachi band. Please inform your family and friends of this upcoming event. We hope to see you there, supporting our students. The funds will help us to buy more intruments like violins, trumpets, guitars, accordions etc.

We hope to see you there. Don't miss out!
